<title>BOLIVIA: SOCCER-BRAZIL BEAT COLOMIA 2-0 IN COPA AMERICA.</title>
<headline>SOCCER-BRAZIL BEAT COLOMIA 2-0 IN COPA AMERICA.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CRUZ, Bolivia 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazil beat</p>
<p>Colombia 2-0 (halftime 1-0) in a Copa America first round</p>
<p>group C game Thursday.</p>
<p>Scorers: Dunga (11th minute), Edmundo (67)</p>
<p>Final first round standings (tabulate under played, won,</p>
<p>drawn, lost, goals for, goals against, points)</p>
<p>Group A</p>
<p> Ecuador	  3  2  1  0  4  1  7</p>
<p> Argentina	3  1  2  0  3  1  5</p>
<p> Paraguay	 3  1  1  1  2  3  4</p>
<p> Chile	    3  0  0  3  1  5  0</p>
<p>Ecuador, Argentina and Paraguay qualify.</p>
<p>Group B</p>
<p> Bolivia	  3  3  0  0  4  0  9</p>
<p> Peru	     3  2  0  1  3  2  6</p>
<p> Uruguay	  3  1  0  2  2  2  3</p>
<p> Venezuela	3  0  0  3  0  5  0</p>
<p>Bolivia and Peru qualify</p>
<p>Group C</p>
<p> Brazil	   3  3  0  0 10  2  9</p>
<p> Mexico	   3  1  1  1  5  5  4</p>
<p> Colombia	 3  1  0  2  5  5  3</p>
<p> Costa Rica     3  0  1  2  2 10  1</p>
<p>Brazil, Mexico and Colombia qualify</p>
<p>Note: Top two teams plus the two third-placed teams with</p>
<p>the best records advance to quarter-finals.</p>
<p>Quarter-finals:</p>
<p>June 21:</p>
<p>In Sucre: Peru v Argentina</p>
<p>In La Paz: Bolivia v Colombia</p>
<p>June 22:</p>
<p>In Cochabamba: Ecuador v Mexico</p>
<p>In Santa Cruz: Brazil v Paraguay</p>
